		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Sorry I'll just chime in and bail (I've had a weird day) -- I don't care what the &quot;effect&quot; is called, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8tN_TPTIrYs&amp;t=1m7s" class="postlink">it fucks with your eyes</a> and takes away from the gameplay big time.  It's the main reason I hated Jim Power on the SNES.  I never had the opportunity to see the Amiga original until many many years after the SNES release, and I still remember my initial reaction: &quot;Holy shit! <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5JHIpbWdKow&amp;t=5m0s" class="postlink">The parallax scrolling makes sense!</a>&quot;<br /><br />Also, and this is for Piko: please make sure Mr. Hülsbeck doesn't give you some kind of soundtrack that's ripped off from either <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xk-kaSEGT0U&amp;t=19m34s" class="postlink">Ys 3</a> (like he did with <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8VcKqKMF130" class="postlink">Jim Power</a>) or <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dKeuMr5hfV0" class="postlink">Transformers: The Movie</a> (like he did with <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NqAsGDgvPyo" class="postlink">Turrican</a>).  Hopefully he learned his lesson...

		

